# Everything in this repo is ultimately consumed on Linux — bash scripts run
# inside C3 containers, source is built in Linux images. CRLF line endings
# (which Git can introduce on a Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true) break
# shell scripts: e.g. `set -euo pipefail\r` makes bash report
# "invalid option name". Force LF on checkout for every OS so clones on Linux,
# macOS, and Windows all produce identical, working files.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Shell scripts must always be LF, never CRLF.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Binary assets: never apply line-ending normalization.
*.png binary
